details.name: Matrix metalloproteinases (MMPs)
details.description: A family of enzymes that help break down the extracellular matrix and are involved in various physiological processes such as tissue remodeling, wound healing, and inflammation.
details.findings: Elevated levels of MMP-2, MMP-3, MMP-7, and MMP-9 have been associated with various inflammatory conditions, including cardiovascular disease, cancer, and neurodegenerative disorders.
details.notes: MMPs are also involved in the regulation of immune responses and have been shown to play a role in the development of autoimmune diseases such as rheumatoid arthritis and multiple sclerosis.

details.name: Tumor necrosis factor-alpha (TNF-α)
details.description: A pro-inflammatory cytokine that plays a key role in the regulation of immune responses and is involved in various physiological processes such as inflammation, cell proliferation, and apoptosis.
details.findings: Elevated levels of TNF-α have been associated with various inflammatory conditions, including cardiovascular disease, cancer, and neurodegenerative disorders.
details.notes: TNF-α is also involved in the regulation of immune responses and has been shown to play a role in the development of autoimmune diseases such as rheumatoid arthritis and multiple sclerosis.

details.name: Interleukin-6 (IL-6)
details.description: A pro-inflammatory cytokine that plays a key role in the regulation of immune responses and is involved in various physiological processes such as inflammation, cell proliferation, and apoptosis.
details.findings: Elevated levels of IL-6 have been associated with various inflammatory conditions, including cardiovascular disease, cancer, and neurodegenerative disorders.
details.notes: IL-6 is also involved in the regulation of immune responses and has been shown to play a role in the development of autoimmune diseases such as rheumatoid arthritis and multiple sclerosis.
